From: LunaOS Project <lunaos@puredarwin.org>
Date: 2026-02-28
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] render: force pixman renderer on Darwin (no GPU accel yet)

On Darwin with IODRMShim, we have dumb framebuffer access but no
OpenGL/Vulkan (IOAcceleratorFamily is closed).  Force the pixman
software renderer which only needs a mappable dumb buffer.

The pixman renderer works by:
  1. Compositor renders to a wlr_buffer (plain malloc'd memory)
  2. pixman blits it to the dumb buffer via CPU
  3. IODRMShim.kext copies dumb buffer to VRAM on SETCRTC

Performance: sufficient for a desktop at 1080p/60hz on modern x86_64.
LLVMpipe EGL can be added later as a drop-in upgrade.
---
diff --git a/render/meson.build b/render/meson.build
--- a/render/meson.build
+++ b/render/meson.build
@@ -1,5 +1,11 @@
+if host_machine.system() == 'darwin'
+  # Darwin: pixman only, no EGL/GLES/Vulkan until GPU driver available
+  conf_data.set('WLR_HAS_GLES2_RENDERER', false)
+  conf_data.set('WLR_HAS_VULKAN_RENDERER', false)
+  conf_data.set('WLR_HAS_PIXMAN_RENDERER', true)
+  subdir('pixman')
+else
 subdir('gles2')
 subdir('vulkan')
 subdir('pixman')
+endif

diff --git a/render/pixman/renderer.c b/render/pixman/renderer.c
--- a/render/pixman/renderer.c
+++ b/render/pixman/renderer.c
@@ -1,4 +1,12 @@
 #include "pixman-renderer-internal.h"
+
+#ifdef __APPLE__
+/* Darwin: map the dumb buffer directly as our render target.
+ * wlr_pixman_renderer_get_buffer() returns the dumb buffer fd,
+ * which we mmap() here for pixman to draw into. */
+#include <sys/mman.h>
+#include "../../backend/drm/darwin/drm_darwin_session.h"
+#endif
